summary: Code reads a log file (base.log), filters out non-empty lines without dots in the first character, converts to a list and stores it in simpleStorage using storeAList function.

details.comment: Code reads a log file (base.log), filters out non-empty lines without dots in the first character, converts to a list and stores it in simpleStorage using storeAList function.
details.content:
from simpleStorage import storeAList
with open("base.log","r") as f:
    storeAList(list(filter((lambda x: x!="" and ('.' not in x ) and ord(x[0])>=97),f.read().split("\n"))))
